Augustus (9/23/63 BC - 8/19/14) Caesar's nephew and heir, the first Emperor of Rome.
Died 19 August AD 14, aged 75, perhaps poisoned by Livia. Afterwards Deified.
Marcus Agrippa (c. 64 BC - 12 BC) Trusted and faithful friend, general and heir to Augustus, Agrippa was the grandfather and great-grandfather of emperors.
Died peacefully but prematurely at age 51.
Tiberius (11/16/42 BC - 3/16/37) Stepson of Augustus, second emperor of Rome.
Gradual withdrawal and decent into depravity until finally perishing AD 37.
Caligula (8/31/12 - 1/24/41) "... So much for Caligula as emperor; we must now tell of his career as a monster..." - Suetonius
Claudius (8/1/10 BC - 10/13/54) Uncle of Caligula, found hiding behind the curtains and declared emperor. Incorporated Britain.
Murdered by wife and niece Agrippina to ensure the succession of her son Nero.
Messalina♀ (c. 17 - 48) Mother of Claudius' son Brittanicus.
Openly married another man. Murdered by a centurian.
Brittanicus (2/12/41 - 2/11/55) Son of Claudius and heir to the throne.
Nero (12/15/37 - 6/9/68) Artist, and last of the Julio-Claudians.
Declared a public enemy by the Senate, fled Rome and ordered servant to kill him, precipitating the Year of the Four Emperors. "What an artist the world is losing!"
Valerian (c. 199 - c. 264) Crisis Emperor, captured by Persians.
In AD 260, decisively defeated and captured alive by Sassanid King Sharpur I, for use as his footstool.
Macrianus Major (259 - 261) Usurper in the east with his sons.
Defeated by Gallienus' general Aureolus in Thrace AD 261.
Macrianus Minor (259 - 261) Usurper in the east with his father and brother.
Defeated by Gallienus' general Aureolus in Thrace AD 261.
Quietus (260 - 261) Usurper in the east with his father and brother.
After his father Macrianus and brother were defeated by Gallienus, Odenathus beseiged Quietus at Emesa and killed by its inhabitants.
Postumus (260 - 269) Emperor of breakaway Gallic Empire. Defended Rhine frontier from Germanic invasions.
Aurelian (9/9/214 - 10/275) Restituto Orbis, the Restorer of the World.
Mistakenly murdered by court officials, AD 275.
Ulpia Severina♀ (c. 220 - c. 280) Ran things durings a brif interregnum following Aurelian's murder.
Abdicated AD 305, forcing Maximian to do the same, and turned to the growing of cabbages.
